Takudzwa Chitsiga Sports Reporter HARARE Province Division Two and Three Leagues will host a football administrators seminar from July 4-6 in the capital. Harare province chairman Robert Tembo said the seminar will be conducted by Premier Soccer League chief executive Kenny Ndebele. We will conduct an administrators seminar in the capital and it is open to all soccer administrators from the Premier League, Division One, Two and Three. The seminar is the second of its kind after we also successfully held one before. The seminar will cover several aspects of football ranging from rules, managing strategies, human resources, finance and marketing. Other issues to be covered will include how to organise major sports and Olympic events, said Tembo.Participants will have to register early for the seminar.